WEBVTT

01:40.490 --> 01:45.930
[Speed and Love]

01:46.270 --> 01:48.820
[Episode 26]

01:53.330 --> 01:54.860
The sun and moon alternate.

01:55.400 --> 01:57.600
Even natural laws aren't absolute—

01:59.580 --> 02:00.870
let alone people.

02:13.720 --> 02:14.670
Do you get

02:15.310 --> 02:16.970
♪ Forgotten between the rearview mirror ♪

02:16.970 --> 02:18.370
what I'm trying to say?

02:22.460 --> 02:27.490
♪ Seeing your long unseen face
on that rainy night ♪

02:27.490 --> 02:28.640
day by day

02:30.170 --> 02:30.800
♪ Counting backwards to
the unfulfilled promises ♪

02:30.800 --> 02:31.840
the moon by night—

02:34.640 --> 02:36.370
Sun and moon shining together,

02:37.180 --> 02:38.490
♪ The heart that is still beating
hasn't said goodbye yet ♪

02:38.490 --> 02:39.800
Zhao and Mu,

02:41.930 --> 02:43.290
never to be separated.

02:43.770 --> 02:46.620
♪ Meeting again after many years ♪

02:47.110 --> 02:50.020
♪ The coffee is too sour and bitter;
I'm greedy for something sweet ♪

02:50.610 --> 02:51.160
This is my answer.

02:51.160 --> 02:53.790
♪ Who will circle around the line
bordering the thoughts? ♪

02:54.150 --> 02:58.280
♪ Stupidly,
I refuse to believe there's an end ♪

02:59.050 --> 03:01.040
♪ I must ♪

03:01.060 --> 03:04.880
♪ Continue to love,
between the sun and the moon ♪

03:04.900 --> 03:08.310
♪ Even in pain,
we indulge in the iron-like vows ♪

03:08.520 --> 03:10.040
♪ Willingly ♪

03:12.660 --> 03:15.880
♪ At this moment ♪

03:16.100 --> 03:19.540
♪ I run towards you
before the night falls ♪

03:19.560 --> 03:24.079
♪ Don't ask about the past;
just bet on tomorrow ♪

03:24.120 --> 03:27.290
♪ Those dreams and longings ♪

03:45.579 --> 03:51.510
♪ I really want to fill
the void of regret ♪

03:52.660 --> 03:55.180
♪ My longing has left the bow ♪

03:55.200 --> 03:59.090
♪ Shooting out into the horizon ♪

03:59.440 --> 04:02.350
♪ Meeting again after many years ♪

04:02.820 --> 04:05.590
♪ The coffee is too sour and bitter;
I'm greedy for something sweet ♪

04:07.020 --> 04:09.650
♪ Who will circle around the line
bordering the thoughts? ♪

04:10.010 --> 04:14.140
♪ Stupidly,
I refuse to believe there's an end ♪

04:14.910 --> 04:16.899
♪ I must ♪

04:16.920 --> 04:20.740
♪ Continue to love,
between the sun and the moon ♪

04:20.760 --> 04:24.170
♪ Even in pain,
we indulge in the iron-like vows ♪

04:24.380 --> 04:25.900
♪ Willingly ♪

04:28.520 --> 04:31.740
♪ At this moment ♪

04:31.950 --> 04:35.390
♪ I run towards you
before the night falls ♪

04:35.420 --> 04:39.940
♪ Don't ask about the past;
just bet on tomorrow ♪

04:40.190 --> 04:42.920
♪ Those dreams and longings ♪

04:42.940 --> 04:47.320
♪ The trails overlap again ♪

05:02.200 --> 05:02.800
Mu!

05:02.880 --> 05:04.310
-Mu.
-Jiang Mu.

05:06.560 --> 05:07.690
Your ex-boyfriend?

05:08.610 --> 05:09.870
My current boyfriend.

05:09.930 --> 05:11.060
Current boyfriend?

05:11.970 --> 05:12.530
Hello.

05:13.320 --> 05:14.360
Allow me to introduce you all.

05:14.360 --> 05:15.880
This is Mu's boyfriend.

05:17.690 --> 05:19.930
-So handsome!
-You should treat us to this meal.

05:19.930 --> 05:20.970
You've taken away the goddess

05:20.970 --> 05:22.680
that so many guys
in our department dream of.

05:22.680 --> 05:24.170
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

05:24.610 --> 05:25.610
This meal is on me.

05:25.750 --> 05:27.010
Eat whatever you want.

05:27.090 --> 05:27.560
Great.

05:28.650 --> 05:30.170
Come on, don't just stand there. Sit down.

05:30.170 --> 05:31.460
Come on.

05:32.080 --> 05:33.340
Hurry, Mu, take a seat.

05:35.560 --> 05:36.409
So, Mu,

05:36.530 --> 05:37.240
when will we get to

05:37.240 --> 05:38.090
attend your wedding?

05:38.090 --> 05:39.360
Yeah, when will it be?

05:39.730 --> 05:41.070
When I met them this afternoon,

05:41.070 --> 05:42.730
they weren't reconciled yet.

05:42.970 --> 05:45.880
Now you're already asking them
about their wedding.

05:45.880 --> 05:46.610
So,

05:46.840 --> 05:47.940
when's the wedding?

05:47.940 --> 05:49.260
-Yeah.
-When?

05:51.090 --> 05:52.610
I'll try to make it happen soon.

05:52.610 --> 05:54.170
Great, it's settled then.

05:54.190 --> 05:55.650
We'll all attend when the time comes.

05:55.650 --> 05:56.930
Come on, let's toast to your happiness.

05:56.930 --> 05:57.970
Cheers.

06:19.690 --> 06:23.050
♪ What was it that brought me to you? ♪

06:23.440 --> 06:25.350
♪ Perhaps it was fate's design ♪

06:25.920 --> 06:29.660
♪ Through all our winding paths,
we always find each other ♪

06:29.680 --> 06:33.280
♪ The storm turned to rain,
and everything was swept away ♪

06:33.310 --> 06:35.020
♪ Slowly, everything becomes clear ♪

06:35.040 --> 06:37.400
♪ In your gaze ♪

06:37.690 --> 06:39.650
♪ I found the answer ♪

06:39.680 --> 06:41.720
♪ There's a feeling so strong ♪

06:41.750 --> 06:44.880
♪ Our story is still unfolding ♪

06:45.020 --> 06:48.930
♪ Waiting for the perfect ending ♪

06:50.640 --> 06:53.090
♪ It all began the moment I met you ♪

06:53.110 --> 06:55.580
♪ There's a pull I cannot explain ♪

06:55.610 --> 06:58.730
♪ My eyes follow you,
my heart chases after you ♪

06:58.750 --> 07:00.560
♪ I just can't help it ♪

07:00.580 --> 07:03.030
♪ When I gaze across the sky ♪

07:03.060 --> 07:05.560
♪ Not even miles can keep us apart ♪

07:05.580 --> 07:08.590
♪ Sweet longing drifts on the wind ♪

07:08.610 --> 07:10.830
♪ I can feel you near ♪

07:11.040 --> 07:12.430
♪ Come with me ♪

07:12.670 --> 07:15.320
♪ Forget the sunsets, forget the tides ♪

07:15.340 --> 07:17.440
♪ Watch the years pass
and wander the world ♪

07:17.460 --> 07:19.570
♪ We've learned to
cherish each other more ♪

07:19.590 --> 07:22.070
♪ It all began the moment I met you ♪

07:22.100 --> 07:24.410
♪ The road ahead ♪

07:24.640 --> 07:26.480
♪ And every step we take ♪

07:26.550 --> 07:29.230
♪ Guide us toward happiness ♪

07:31.500 --> 07:35.430
♪ We'll both be there ♪

07:39.290 --> 07:40.290
It's fine.

07:41.220 --> 07:42.020
It's raining.

07:42.440 --> 07:43.000
Come on.

07:43.170 --> 07:44.120
We had a great time today.

07:44.120 --> 07:45.240
Let's get together again soon.

07:45.240 --> 07:45.930
We're leaving first!

07:45.930 --> 07:47.880
Bye-bye.

07:48.490 --> 07:49.550
I was just kidding.

07:49.560 --> 07:51.350
You actually paid for everything.

07:51.350 --> 07:51.700
It's my pleasure.

07:51.700 --> 07:53.409
Thank you so much for the meal.

07:53.440 --> 07:55.000
We’re leaving.
Thank you so much.

07:55.000 --> 07:55.610
Bye.
Bye.

07:55.630 --> 07:57.200
-Take care on your way.
-Bye-bye.

07:57.200 --> 07:58.850
-Bye-bye.
-Bye-bye.

08:02.650 --> 08:03.600
The rain is so heavy.

08:03.600 --> 08:05.330
We can't drive 'cause we drank.

08:05.360 --> 08:06.360
What should we do?

08:09.000 --> 08:10.660
It's not far. Let's walk back.

08:11.200 --> 08:12.800
But we don't have umbrellas.

08:23.100 --> 08:24.760
I can't see the road like this.

08:25.450 --> 08:26.650
I'm here. Stay close.

08:26.720 --> 08:27.610
Don't get wet.

08:31.410 --> 08:33.270
You're not abducting me, are you?

08:33.830 --> 08:34.500
Who knows?

08:56.650 --> 08:57.480
Look at you.

08:57.890 --> 08:58.900
You're soaking wet.

08:58.900 --> 09:01.360
Go take a shower quickly.
Don't catch a cold.

09:03.130 --> 09:05.130
Okay. Wait for me in the living room.

10:05.120 --> 10:05.810
You saw it?

10:08.800 --> 10:11.330
How long did it take
for you to put it together?

10:12.480 --> 10:13.680
Adding up both times,

10:14.550 --> 10:15.350
quite a while.

10:16.800 --> 10:17.720
Two times?

10:22.080 --> 10:24.080
When it was being transported here,

10:25.250 --> 10:26.370
it fell apart once.

10:27.960 --> 10:29.080
When I moved it here and reassembled it,

10:29.080 --> 10:30.810
I lost the instruction manual.

10:31.350 --> 10:33.410
The second time was quite difficult.

11:15.130 --> 11:16.590
What about the other time?

11:30.170 --> 11:31.170
The first time...

11:34.240 --> 11:36.500
That was when you had just gone to Canada.

11:36.860 --> 11:38.590
I was confined to a wheelchair.

11:39.200 --> 11:40.400
The pills I had to take

11:40.600 --> 11:41.930
were more than my meals.

11:43.250 --> 11:45.110
Besides enduring the pain daily,

11:46.130 --> 11:47.200
I also had to endure

11:47.890 --> 11:49.090
the days without you.

11:50.760 --> 11:51.880
Back then, I

11:52.490 --> 11:54.550
was not looking forward to tomorrow,

11:55.080 --> 11:57.010
and had no idea where my future lay.

11:58.010 --> 11:58.960
This Lego set

11:59.600 --> 12:02.530
kept me company through
those long, difficult days.

12:02.890 --> 12:04.080
It felt like

12:04.960 --> 12:06.560
you were right there with me.

12:08.130 --> 12:11.260
That was the first time
I desperately wanted to stand up.

12:12.960 --> 12:14.290
And from that moment on,

12:15.640 --> 12:17.700
I was filled with hope for the future.

12:33.080 --> 12:34.480
I always thought

12:37.480 --> 12:39.930
we would build these models together.

12:47.600 --> 12:48.960
Back then, I believed

12:50.170 --> 12:52.170
we had plenty of time

12:52.560 --> 12:53.760
to build them slowly.

12:56.290 --> 12:57.130
How about

13:00.440 --> 13:01.600
we take it apart

13:03.290 --> 13:04.890
and build it for a third time?

13:08.800 --> 13:10.130
That's not what I meant.

13:10.890 --> 13:12.720
I just feel a bit regretful.

13:23.340 --> 13:24.410
Who's Thomas?

13:34.650 --> 13:37.110
He's a brilliant student
in our department—

13:37.250 --> 13:39.110
half-Australian, half-French.

13:52.630 --> 13:53.690
He's pursuing you?

13:57.100 --> 13:58.460
I've told you before—

13:59.000 --> 14:00.860
lots of guys are interested in me,

14:01.280 --> 14:02.810
you just didn't believe it.

14:19.660 --> 14:20.520
I do believe it.

14:30.540 --> 14:30.970
Then can I

14:30.970 --> 14:33.510
♪ Faded light that pulls me far ♪

14:33.510 --> 14:34.750
stay here tonight?

14:36.480 --> 14:39.760
♪ Chase the whispers where you are ♪

14:42.080 --> 14:45.280
♪ Through the echoing that still string ♪

14:47.630 --> 14:50.760
♪ Every step takes me away ♪

14:51.820 --> 14:57.330
♪ Away from the noise,
the endless fights ♪

14:58.290 --> 14:59.960
♪  Through the quiet of your light ♪

14:59.960 --> 15:01.560
I'll help you move tomorrow.

15:03.460 --> 15:03.720
♪ I'll break the chains
and leave the gray ♪

15:03.720 --> 15:05.530
Why can they stay here

15:07.680 --> 15:08.680
but I can't?

15:09.480 --> 15:15.290
♪ Take me far, just take me away ♪

15:18.130 --> 15:19.480
♪ Wind is howling and calling me ♪

15:19.480 --> 15:20.290
Fine.

15:22.960 --> 15:23.010
♪ Through the forest to the sea ♪

15:23.010 --> 15:24.050
In that case,

15:24.480 --> 15:25.530
I'll be going now.

15:29.010 --> 15:29.080
♪ Shadows dance, the sky's turned grey ♪

15:29.080 --> 15:30.080
See you next time.

15:34.660 --> 15:38.400
♪ But your voice still leads my ♪

15:39.410 --> 15:40.180
You're not speaking your mind.

15:40.180 --> 15:45.690
♪ Away from the noise,
the endless fights ♪

15:46.470 --> 15:50.590
♪  Through the quiet of your light ♪

15:51.690 --> 15:52.890
♪ I'll break the chains of life's gray ♪

15:52.890 --> 15:54.680
Where am I sleeping tonight?

15:56.930 --> 15:57.710
On the couch?

15:57.710 --> 16:03.520
♪ Take me far, just take me away ♪

16:04.640 --> 16:08.310
♪ Wind is howling and calling me ♪

16:08.560 --> 16:12.470
♪ You're waiting for me come away ♪

16:13.670 --> 16:15.700
♪ Away from the noise,
the endless fights ♪

16:15.700 --> 16:16.500
It's up to you.

16:20.100 --> 16:24.970
♪  Through the quiet of your light ♪

16:25.420 --> 16:30.160
♪ I'll break the chains of life's gray ♪

16:31.430 --> 16:34.370
♪ Take me far, just take me away ♪

16:34.370 --> 16:36.100
Are you really sure about this?

16:36.320 --> 16:37.650
I've told you before,

16:39.200 --> 16:40.930
I'm not a child anymore.

16:58.550 --> 16:59.610
Why are you hiding?

17:09.450 --> 17:10.579
Too shy to look at me?

17:12.020 --> 17:12.750
No, I'm not.

17:16.369 --> 17:17.230
Then look at me.

19:53.290 --> 19:54.120
You're awake.

19:57.110 --> 19:58.280
Did you sleep well?

20:09.890 --> 20:11.350
When do you want to move in?

20:13.170 --> 20:15.430
My lease isn't up until two months later.

20:15.610 --> 20:17.270
I can't just waste that money.

20:32.410 --> 20:34.070
Why did you transfer me money?

20:35.110 --> 20:37.650
Consider it as
you've sublet it to me for two months.

20:37.650 --> 20:38.710
Can you move in now?

20:44.740 --> 20:46.540
Someone's here to help you move.

20:51.500 --> 20:52.130
Boss,

20:52.410 --> 20:53.910
do we get overtime pay for weekends?

20:53.910 --> 20:54.520
Yes.

20:57.690 --> 20:58.490
Isn't this...

21:01.350 --> 21:02.710
Hello, I'm Wen Ke.

21:02.860 --> 21:03.790
Just call me Wen.

21:04.500 --> 21:05.130
Hello.

21:05.590 --> 21:06.850
Are you his colleague?

21:07.610 --> 21:09.610
I'm Mr. Jin's assistant and driver.

21:11.520 --> 21:13.650
Mr. Jin, I'll wait for you downstairs.

21:15.300 --> 21:15.860
Bye-bye.

21:20.230 --> 21:21.890
So you planned this all along.

21:44.320 --> 21:45.010
Wen.

21:45.450 --> 21:46.700
Wait in the car for a while.

21:46.700 --> 21:48.380
Come up
after we've packed her things.

21:48.380 --> 21:48.900
Okay.

21:54.340 --> 21:55.780
So you have a driver now?

21:55.930 --> 21:57.460
Why does he call you Mr. Jin?

21:57.930 --> 21:59.130
Didn't Da Jia and Xiao Jia say

21:59.130 --> 22:01.130
you aren't working for any company?

22:01.200 --> 22:03.630
What do you do on your business trips?

22:05.100 --> 22:06.930
Why do you have so many questions?

22:06.930 --> 22:08.780
Of course I need to ask.

22:08.930 --> 22:10.690
I can't be with you without knowing

22:10.690 --> 22:12.020
what your situation is.

22:13.690 --> 22:15.820
Then why didn't you ask last night

22:16.090 --> 22:18.750
before getting together
with me so carelessly?

22:20.630 --> 22:22.330
In a situation like last night,

22:22.330 --> 22:23.410
how could I ask?

22:29.920 --> 22:30.920
This is my home.

22:31.300 --> 22:32.700
Feel free to look around.

22:34.300 --> 22:35.300
Where was I?

22:36.050 --> 22:37.710
Last time my drain was broken.

22:37.970 --> 22:40.060
I was going to call the landlord.

22:40.650 --> 22:42.580
But my roommate is really nice.

22:43.170 --> 22:44.740
He called his friend to come over.

22:44.740 --> 22:46.860
That friend fixed it in no time.

22:48.370 --> 22:50.930
And then that friend stayed overnight.

22:51.690 --> 22:52.620
How did you know?

22:53.260 --> 22:53.990
Just a guess.

22:56.310 --> 22:58.030
Let's start moving. How should we do it?

22:58.030 --> 22:58.830
I'll help you.

23:00.640 --> 23:02.840
How do we move?

23:05.540 --> 23:07.370
I don't know where to start.

23:07.540 --> 23:09.170
I hate packing things up.

23:10.860 --> 23:11.820
I'll do it from now on.

23:11.820 --> 23:12.370
No way!

23:12.650 --> 23:13.540
If you do everything,

23:13.540 --> 23:15.000
won't I seem too high-maintenance?

23:15.000 --> 23:16.300
What's wrong with being high-maintenance?

23:16.300 --> 23:17.700
I'll indulge you anyway.

23:18.690 --> 23:19.580
Really?

23:19.890 --> 23:21.890
How long do you plan on indulging me?

23:23.060 --> 23:23.780
A lifetime.

23:43.780 --> 23:45.890
Do you always pack up by yourself?

23:46.660 --> 23:47.380
What else?

23:48.890 --> 23:51.420
What about Wen?
Has he been with you all along?

23:51.700 --> 23:54.510
A few years ago, I went to work
at a factory in Beijing.

23:54.510 --> 23:55.620
After making a name for myself,

23:55.620 --> 23:58.060
I went
to the Automotive Engineering Institute

23:58.060 --> 24:00.740
to work on technical engineering
innovations with them.

24:00.740 --> 24:02.600
As for me,
I wanted to work on some small projects,

24:02.600 --> 24:04.000
so I opened a coffee shop.

24:04.020 --> 24:05.930
I've been a free agent,

24:07.080 --> 24:09.740
while collaborating with them
as a consultant.

24:11.370 --> 24:13.370
At minimum,
I have to go there twice a month.

24:13.370 --> 24:14.740
At most, I go every week.

24:15.020 --> 24:16.610
Considering my health condition,

24:16.610 --> 24:17.340
a few years ago,

24:17.340 --> 24:18.780
they assigned me an assistant,

24:18.780 --> 24:19.820
who is Wen,

24:20.050 --> 24:22.980
mainly responsible for handling
my business trips.

24:27.290 --> 24:28.780
Are all the scarves packed?

24:28.780 --> 24:29.580
Yes.

24:34.860 --> 24:35.990
I found another one.

24:40.130 --> 24:41.230
That's not a scarf.

24:41.260 --> 24:42.370
It's my skirt.

24:46.000 --> 24:47.060
Where are the sleeves?

24:47.060 --> 24:48.460
It doesn't need sleeves.

24:48.780 --> 24:50.110
It's a strapless dress.

24:50.210 --> 24:51.740
You just put it on directly.

24:58.100 --> 24:59.160
I can't picture it.

25:01.290 --> 25:02.050
Try it on.

26:17.850 --> 26:18.980
[Record of my Life]

26:33.090 --> 26:33.650
Don't go.

26:35.840 --> 26:37.970
We don't have a single photo together.

26:38.130 --> 26:39.930
Why don't we take this opportunity?

26:39.930 --> 26:41.300
Let me set a timer.

29:35.910 --> 29:36.830
Let me ask you.

29:38.860 --> 29:39.780
When do you

29:40.310 --> 29:41.280
usually wear

29:41.500 --> 29:43.010
this outfit?

29:49.070 --> 29:50.550
When I meet handsome guys.

29:56.560 --> 29:58.220
What makes someone handsome?

30:00.600 --> 30:01.330
Do I qualify?

30:05.060 --> 30:06.920
Wen is still waiting downstairs.

30:12.770 --> 30:13.490
Wen,

30:14.540 --> 30:16.140
it'll take us a little longer.

30:16.140 --> 30:18.400
Go back to the coffee shop
and wait for me.

30:20.440 --> 30:21.970
He might get the wrong idea.

30:21.970 --> 30:22.600
He won't.

30:22.980 --> 30:23.700
Why not?

30:28.820 --> 30:29.950
Because in his eyes,

30:30.490 --> 30:31.950
I'm a respectable person.

30:50.650 --> 30:51.910
It should be this room.

30:58.090 --> 30:58.820
Mr. Jin?

31:01.110 --> 31:01.800
Mr. Jin?

31:05.560 --> 31:06.760
Why is everyone here?

31:07.100 --> 31:08.820
Seeing how you were taking so long,

31:08.820 --> 31:10.370
I thought you had a lot of stuff to pack.

31:10.370 --> 31:11.630
I even called Xiao Jia.

31:13.390 --> 31:15.480
There are quite a few things.
We were just careful with our packing.

31:15.480 --> 31:16.000
Here.

31:17.000 --> 31:18.200
Thanks for your help.

31:18.670 --> 31:19.430
Thank you.

31:21.900 --> 31:22.900
And this one, too.

31:25.100 --> 31:25.610
Here. Be careful.

31:25.610 --> 31:27.740
I don't know how he manages to do it.

31:28.140 --> 31:29.650
Lying so shamelessly

31:29.650 --> 31:30.930
with a straight face.

31:53.390 --> 31:54.720
Ms. Jiang, you're here.

31:55.610 --> 31:56.420
Ms. Jiang?

31:58.650 --> 31:59.650
It's Boss Lady.

32:00.140 --> 32:02.270
Would you like some coffee?

32:03.370 --> 32:04.490
It's fine. You can go about your business.

32:04.490 --> 32:05.950
I just stopped by on my way.

32:06.000 --> 32:07.380
I need to go home for dinner soon.

32:07.380 --> 32:07.950
Okay.

32:16.680 --> 32:17.850
Here's the account book.

32:17.850 --> 32:20.110
All the operations details are in there.

32:23.690 --> 32:25.290
Why are you giving this to me?

32:26.270 --> 32:27.210
It's your own shop.

32:27.210 --> 32:29.410
You should at least know how it's doing.

32:29.580 --> 32:30.540
My shop?

32:32.300 --> 32:33.740
Since when is it my shop?

32:35.780 --> 32:37.170
Why else would I bother?

32:37.410 --> 32:39.670
Do you think opening a coffee shop is fun?

32:42.130 --> 32:43.990
When I first returned to Nanjing,

32:44.210 --> 32:46.270
I started planning this coffee shop.

32:47.050 --> 32:48.960
I participated
in designing the environment

32:48.960 --> 32:50.760
and coming up with the shop name.

33:02.430 --> 33:03.490
This place is nice.

33:03.650 --> 33:04.740
Thank you for your recommendation.

33:04.740 --> 33:05.870
I'm very satisfied.

33:06.970 --> 33:08.830
We can sign the contract anytime.

33:09.400 --> 33:10.770
Sure. Thanks.

33:56.850 --> 33:57.960
I've already sent you

33:57.960 --> 34:00.010
the font for the signature coffee logo.

34:00.010 --> 34:00.940
Use the same font

34:01.960 --> 34:03.290
for the signboard, too.

34:03.860 --> 34:04.500
Moon.

34:05.930 --> 34:06.700
Moon Coffee.

34:25.750 --> 34:28.790
But I heard that for the first two years,

34:29.139 --> 34:30.739
this place was losing money.

34:35.580 --> 34:37.010
Different trades are worlds apart.

34:37.010 --> 34:38.210
I made some mistakes.

34:39.780 --> 34:40.820
Then why

34:40.820 --> 34:42.750
did you keep pouring money into it?

34:43.290 --> 34:44.210
Because

34:46.600 --> 34:49.130
a young girl suggested it
to me many years ago.

34:51.010 --> 34:52.409
I'm a very honest person—

34:52.659 --> 34:53.659
almost stubborn.

34:54.090 --> 34:55.840
I believe the more mistakes I make,

34:55.840 --> 34:57.660
the more I will find the right path
eventually.

34:57.660 --> 34:59.060
Even if one day it closes,

34:59.220 --> 35:01.680
it shouldn't be because
of poor management.

35:03.920 --> 35:05.380
You call yourself honest?

35:05.740 --> 35:08.670
Then why did you corner me
against the wall back then?

35:09.320 --> 35:10.780
When did I ever corner you?

35:11.660 --> 35:12.620
At the garage.

35:13.220 --> 35:14.280
You told me to leave

35:14.410 --> 35:17.210
and said it looked bad
that I kept coming to see you.

35:17.300 --> 35:18.490
You even asked

35:18.780 --> 35:20.780
if I wanted something more with you.

35:25.090 --> 35:26.620
I was just asking casually.

35:27.490 --> 35:28.140
Just...

35:42.340 --> 35:42.940
What?

35:44.540 --> 35:45.540
Did I hit a nerve?

35:47.860 --> 35:49.260
Sorry to disappoint you.

36:10.140 --> 36:11.060
Okay, got it.

36:17.600 --> 36:18.280
Mu.

36:18.810 --> 36:20.940
I need to go on an urgent business trip.

36:21.010 --> 36:22.270
Wen will take you home.

36:24.180 --> 36:25.520
Be good and wait for me at home,

36:25.520 --> 36:26.220
okay?
